properties.Name: ChannelOrderCommission
properties.Description:
Commissions that are assigned or awarded to Channels in conjunction with the associated Order.

Note:
Both a sales and distribution channel may receive commissions upon the same order, which is why both Order ID and Channel ID are part of the key.

Columns.Name: ChannelId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Channel.

Columns.Name: TransactionId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Transaction.

Columns.Name: CommissionAwardedDate
Columns.Description: The assignment or crediting date of the Commissions.

Columns.Name: CommissionDueDate
Columns.Description: The date that the Commissions are due to the Employee.

Columns.Name: OrderCommissionBasisAmount
Columns.Description: The amount upon which the Commission is calculated.

Columns.Name: OrderCommissionPercentage
Columns.Description: The percentage used to calculate the Commission.

Columns.Name: SplitCommissionIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the Commissions are split between two or more Employees.
